products.title: SK61S RGB Optical Mechanical Keyboard
products.body_html:
FEATURES

  • RGB Backlit Optical Mechanical Switches.
  • 60% Keyboard.
  • IP68 Waterproof / Dustproof Rating.
  • Long Key Lifespan.
  • Hotswappable.
  • Full-Key Programmable.
  • User-Defined Fn Keys.
  • Lighting Effect Library.

THE SWITCHES

Blue Switch
This switch feels tactile and clicky with a bump feel. It is a bit noisier than the Brown Switch, making it the option more suitable for general typing and gaming purposes.

Brown Switch
The switch feels less clicky, making it a better choice to be used in an office environment. Some people prefer Brown Switch since it enables you to double tap faster and typists like them because they still have good tactile feedback yet quieter than the Blue Switch.

Red Switch
This switch feels linear and smooth, meaning that the force at the beginning and the end of each stroke is nearly identical. It is mostly perceived as faster among gaming enthusiasts.

PACKAGE

1 x USB-C Cable
1 x User Manual

products.title: LDSA Low Profile Blank Keycaps - Group Buy
products.body_html:
Are you ready for a new low profile, Kailh Choc-compatible keycap? Then let us introduce you to our latest product, the LDSA profile keycap.

LDSA stands for Low profile DSA, so it stands to reason that this keycap is a uniform-profile spherical keycap. The profile was designed by Lowprokb, inspired by the popular DSA keycap profile. It has a deep comfortable scoop, and soft edges to prevent edge pain, and a textured finger contact region to add comfort and prevent slippage.

LDSA is injected molded out of premium PBT plastic, so they are very resistant to the wear and "shining" caused by many hours of typing. The kit includes 50 keycaps in the following sizes:

  • 2x - 1.5u thumbs (horizontal)
  • 4x - 1u thumbs
  • 2x - 1u homing
  • 42x - 1u

Not in the UK?

  • EU: Qweebs
  • AU/NZ: KEEBD
  • US: Lowprokb.ca

notes:

  • These keycaps are intended as a proof of concept. It is the ultimate goal to produce dual-shot legended keycaps, but first the profile must be proven. If you purchase LDSA keycaps, please let us know what you thought of them.
  • As these are first-run samples, there are some small issues with them: 1) the fit of the stems into the keycaps are a bit tight. If you feel they are too tight, the issue is easily mitigated by quick scrape on all 4 sides of the stems with a blade. 2) to keep costs down, the sprues were not removed at the factory, but clipped off by us prior to shipping. There may be small bumps on the sides of the keycaps that you may have to scrape/sand to get perfectly smooth.
  • LDSA keycaps are "choc spaced" meaning they do not share the same outer dimensions of a typical Cherry MX keycap. The switch spacing should ideally be 17(h)x18(w) on your keyboard.

products.title: Corne-ish Zen
products.body_html:
The Corne-ish Zen is a premium, ultra-portable, and incredibly low profile wireless split mechanical keyboard.
It is inspired by the very popular CRKBD (Corne) keyboard designed by the talented Foostan. We changed almost everything about it, but it's heritage is obvious.

Corne-ish Zen Features:

  • Fully assembled! No soldering required! Just add your favourite Kailh choc v1 (PG1350) switches and keycaps... or bundle them with your order and have them installed by us.
  • Choc 18mm x 17mm switch spacing, minimizing gaps between keys
  • Fully assembled PCB with all components and hot-swap sockets pre-soldered
  • PCBs support 3x6 and 3x5 layout configurations utilizing a pinky column that snaps off
  • Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE) 5.0 module with CE, FCC, and RoHS Certifications. This module uses the Nordic NRF52840 SOC which has a 32-bit ARM Cortex-M4 CPU on board running at 64MHz
  • CNC aluminum case machined from a solid billet of 6061 aluminum
  • Injection molded smoked acrylic baseplate (3x6 only)
  • Injection molded black ABS baseplate (3x5 only)
  • ZMK firmware preinstalled
  • Built-in 1.05” E-paper screen on each half. Standard status screen is customizable in ZMK
  • I80mAh lithium polymer batteries included and installed in each half
  • USB C charging ports with ESD protection on data and power lines
  • Keyboard can be operated over USB by connecting left half to host computer. The left and right halves always communicate wirelessly
  • Price includes a travel case to carry your Zen with you wherever you go.

Group Buy Details:

  • This group buy is unlimited and will run for 30 days.
  • Group buy starts: April 24, 2022
  • Group buy ends: May 24, 2022
  • Estimated ship date: Starting August/September
  • Orders will be prepared/assembled/tested/packaged/shipped in order of order number, in groups of 100. This means the lowest 100 order numbers will be shipped before orders 101-200 are prepared

https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1_WPUHEfFfsYUqykvi9sH1rxBQELqpDIK6XhFmgdiAkU


General Group Buy FAQ

  • What is a group buy?
    Group Buys are a method of sale similar to a pre-order where economies of scale are taken advantage of to lower prices. Payments are collected ahead of time in order to submit a bulk order to a manufacturer for production. For this reason, group buy products are not shipped out immediately at time of sale, but after the product has been shipped to us from the manufacturers.
  • How accurate are your estimated timelines?
    We do our best to accurately estimate timelines, but delays can happen due to unexpected (covid anyone?) issues. If a problem occurs that will cause a delay, participants will be notified.
  • Can I get a refund for my Group Buy purchase? I changed my mind.
    In general, no. The nature of the group buy process means that funds for refunds are not available after we pay the manufacturers/suppliers. It will be at our sole discretion to offer a refund to any participant of a group buy.
  • I have my Zen, where can I learn how to use it?
    There is a dedicated Corne-ish Zen support page now: https://lowprokb.ca/pages/corne-ish-zen-support

products.title: Linear A keycaps
products.body_html:
The Linear A keycaps we made for the Model 01 have been incredibly popular. We're excited to announce that we've designed and manufactured Linear A keycaps that will look and feel great on the Atreus (or, indeed, on any keyboard that uses Cherry MX style keyswitches.)

These new XDA-profile keycaps are injection molded from PBT, dyesubbed black, and then laser-ablated to reveal warm white legends.

The full keycap set is 132 keys, including five different full-size space bars, ISO and "Big-ass" Enter keys, and a variety of extras.

The XDA keycap profile means each row has the same spherical sculpted top shape. While we've picked out symbols that are reminiscent of the English alphabet, you can rearrange the keys to any layout you choose. Of course, since the ancient Cretan civilization that created the Linear A alphabet vanished thousands of years ago and modern scholars have yet to decipher the writing system, there's no wrong way to arrange these keycaps.

Note: Keyboard and keyswitches are not included.
